  "text": "In 2015, a prototype moving target detection system was constructed for the robot using an SoC. [CITATION_1] The Gaussian background model was used for foreground detection and a customized accelerator was designed to ensure real-time image processing. However, the framework of the prototype system was coarse and inefficient, which resulted in a high CPU workload and a slow response speed of the robotic control system. Besides, the adopted power optimization methods were not effective enough, which limited its applications in practical scenarios.",
